        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ændaʒyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ændaʒyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>ændæǧd</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ændaʒun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>ændaǧd</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>припаивать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to solder</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>прилеплять</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to stick</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>приклеивать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to glue</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>прикреплять</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to fasten</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>æxsargard duwwæ ænbesi raxawdtæj..., Kurdalægon sæ næwægæj ændaʒun
                            bajdædta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>меч сломился на две половинки, Курдалагон снова стал их спаивать</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the sword broke into two parts, Kurdalagon began to braze it together
                                again.</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Диг._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>16</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Cæraj Farizety k˳y fedta, wæd yl jæ cæstytæ bandæǧta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>когда Царай увидел Фаризет, он устремил на нее взгляд (прилепил к ней
                                свои глаза)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>when Caraj saw Farizet, he stared at her (lit. he sticked his eyes to
                                her)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."
                            /><biblScope>129</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Из %iæm-taʒyn%i, сращение %iæm-%i с глаголом <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_taʒyn"/>, бытующим и самостоятельно в значении ‘капать’,
                    ‘лить по каплям’; <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>æm-taʒ-</w></mentioned> ← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>ham-tač-</w></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>hantačaiti</w>
                        <gloss><q>изливается (вместе)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сливается</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>hantačina</w>
                        <gloss><q>вместе текущий</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*antāč-(ʽntʼč-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>‘скопление’</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>andāxtan : andāz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>бросать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>наливать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>вливать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>vədāɤ-</w>
                        <gloss><q>смешивать</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                    258</biblScope></bibl>). Развитие значения: ‘лить’ → ‘плавить’→ ‘паять’ →
                    ‘клеить’. По огласовке и значению <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ændaʒyn"/>
                    представляет каузатив к <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ændæʒyn"/> Ср. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ændæʒyn"/> ‘прилипать’ и д. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_rædaʒun"/>. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_taʒyn"
                            />.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl></etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">From %iæm-taʒyn%i, the fusion of %iæm-%i with the verb <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_taʒyn"/> being used in the meaning ‘to drop’, ‘to
                    pour drop by drop’; <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>*æm-taʒ-</w></mentioned> ← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w/>
                        <gloss><q>*ham-tač-</q></gloss></mentioned>, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>hantačaiti</w>
                        <gloss><q>streams (together)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>flows together</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>hantačina</w>
                        <gloss><q>flowing together</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*antāč-(ʽntʼč-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>accumulation</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>andāxtan : andāz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to throw</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>to poor</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>to poor in</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>vədāɤ-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to
                            mix</q></gloss></mentioned>(<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><biblScope>IIFL
                            II)</biblScope></bibl>. The development of the meaning: ‘to pour’ → ‘to
                    melt’→ ‘to solder’ → ‘to glue’. As for its vocalism and meaning, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ændaʒyn"/> is a causative form to <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ændæʒyn"/>. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ændæʒyn"/>ˈto
                    stickˈ and Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rædaʒun"/> . Cf. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_taʒyn"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl></etym>
            </entry>
